// Semantic direction:
// transformer is the dominant architecture for sequence modeling via global oppmerksomhet.
// skalert_dot_produkt computes QKᵀ/√d_k, preventing vanishing gradients for large d_k.
// kausal_maske prevents position i from attending to positions > i during autoregressive generation.
// multi_hode_oppmerksomhet runs h parallel attention heads, each learning different patterns.
// grouped_query_attention uses fewer KV heads than Q heads, reducing KV cache memory.
// rope (Rotary Positional Embedding) encodes positions by rotating query/key vectors in 2D planes.
// rope_frekvenser are the θ frequencies: θ_i = 10000^(-2i/d), giving different rates per dimension.
// alibi_koding adds a linear bias -m|i-j| to attention scores, enabling length extrapolation.
// swiglu is the FFN activation used in LLaMA: SiLU(W₁x) ⊙ W₂x, replacing standard ReLU FFN.
// flash_oppmerksomhet computes attention in O(n) memory by tiling and fusing operations.
// sliding_window_oppmerksomhet limits each token to attend to only the w nearest tokens.
// kv_cache stores key/value projections to avoid recomputation during autoregressive decoding.
// paged_oppmerksomhet manages KV cache with virtual pages to handle variable-length batches.
// linear_oppmerksomhet approximates softmax attention with kernel functions for O(n) complexity.
// performer uses random_feature_approks of softmax to compute linear-complexity attention.
// yarn_metode extends RoPE to much longer contexts via temperature-based frequency scaling.

// Primitive flow:
// Scaled dot-product attention:
//   scores = QKᵀ / √d_k -> mask(scores) -> softmax -> A = softmax(scores)*V
// Multi-head: split Q,K,V → h hoder → attention per hode → concat → Wₒ
// Flash Attention v2: del Q,K,V i blokker -> O(n) minne
//   for hvert Q-blokk: beregn attention mot alle K,V-blokker med online softmax
//   akkumuler i SRAM -> skriv resultat til HBM
// Autoregressive generering med KV-cache:
//   prefill: kjør alle tokens → lagre K,V for hvert lag
//   dekoding: kjør kun ny token → les K,V fra cache → gen neste token

// This defines transformers: scaled dot-product attention, multi-head with GQA/MQA,
// positional encodings (RoPE/ALiBi), transformer block variants (pre-LN, SwiGLU),
// major architectures (BERT/GPT/T5/LLaMA), Flash Attention, KV cache management,
// and efficient attention approximations.
